The paper deals with a map matching problem in which a given curve in R^2 needs to be matched with a path in an embedded graph. This problem involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of determining the existence of a simple cycle in a planar straight-line embedding of a graph, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DM) to solve the map matching problem.
